e of the Chinese language is required  Topics in Explosive Chemical Warfare Information Security Technology An Introduction to Marine Vehicle Design Design Methodology of Aerial Vehicles Geospatial Data Processing Advance Light Source in Taiwan  Infrared Optical Principles and Processing Room and Board Students will be living with CCIT cadets in their barracks  Cadets will wear the class uniform  They will be able to participate in physical training and other aspects of daily life at CCIT  Cadets are exposed to many aspects of Taiwanes culture  Excursions in the past have included trips to Taipei  Longshaun Temple  Taipei 101  the Shi lin Night Market  and Sun Moon Lake  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   CCIT Summer Program in Taiwan       Virginia Military Institute   CCIT Summer Program in Taiwan                     skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Scien